Package com.neebal.android.simplyreliable.message

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    BaseCallback
    A base interface that represents the various callbacks that can be called at the time of receiving a response from the server, for a particular type of Message
    Classes wishing to get a handle of the response must implement this callback.
    DeleteMessageCallback
    Interface that represents the various callbacks that can be called at the time of receiving a response for a DeleteMessage.
    GetMessageCallback
    Interface that represents the various callbacks that can be called at the time of receiving a response for a GetMessage.
    HeadMessageCallback
    Interface that represents the various callbacks that can be called at the time of receiving a response for a HeadMessage.
    MultiPartGetMessageCallback
    Interface that represents the various callbacks that can be called at the time of receiving a response for a MultiPartGetMessage.
    PostMessageCallback
    Interface that represents the various callbacks that can be called at the time of receiving a response for a PostMessage.
    PutMessageCallback
    Interface that represents the various callbacks that can be called at the time of receiving a response for a PutMessage.
    RedirectionCallback
    Interface that represents the various callbacks that can be called at the time of receiving a response for a Message with redirection headers from the server
    SimplyReliableMsgIntf Deprecated
    Consider using the new callbacks api.
    StreamingResponseCallback
    Interface that represents the various callbacks that can be called at the time of receiving a response for a Message where the response will not be un-marshalled from JSON to Java object representation.
    UpdateMsgComponentsIntf
    An interface that defines the contract that a Message instance should follow for cases where some of the components of it depends upon the completion of some other Message instance.
    A Resource path of the Message instance could depend upon the completion of another Message instance that it depends upon.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    InternalMessage
    Represents a message instance used by the API for its own internal working.
    Message
    An abstract representation of a Message that can be sent to the server.
    MessageDependency
    A wrapper class that represents a Message instance that a particular Message instance may be dependent upon before it can be sent to the server and whether the Message instance's dependency is fullfilled or no.
    MessageFactory
    Represents a singleton factory instance that will be used to handle the creation/saving/destroying of the various OutMessage instances.
    OutMessage
    An abstract representation of an outgoing message that needs to be sent to the server
    OutMessageState
    The base state class that represents the various states through which a particular OutMessage instance goes through.
